         <abstract id="aspace_fe2af399d7d4c9fd68fc63bbf47a2c35">The papers consist of correspondence, diaries, writings, clippings, photographs, and topical files documenting the career of Benjamin Frank Heintzleman, particularly his term as territorial governor of Alaska (1953-1957) and his work promoting industrial growth and economic development in Alaska.</abstract>
